<div class="content"><nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/hvac/">HVAC</a> › HVAC Van Wraps Chicago</nav><h1>HVAC Van Wraps in Chicago</h1><p class="lead speakable">Chicago Fleet Wraps specializes in HVAC van wraps for heating and cooling companies across Chicago and Chicagoland. Your service vans spend hours parked in residential driveways during installations and repairs — every job site becomes a neighborhood billboard generating thousands of impressions. We wrap cargo vans, sprinter vans, pickup trucks, and box trucks with premium Avery Dennison and 3M cast vinyl rated for Chicago's extreme seasons.</p><div class="cta-bar"><a href="/estimate/" class="btn btn-primary">Get an HVAC Van Wrap Quote →</a><a href="tel:+13125971286" class="btn" style="border-color:var(--gold);color:var(--gold)">📞 Call Now</a></div><div class="trust"><span>📅 <strong>24+ Years</strong> Experience</span><span>🏆 <strong>9,400+</strong> Vehicles Wrapped</span><span>✅ <strong>Avery & 3M</strong> Certified</span><span>🔧 <strong>200+</strong> HVAC Fleets Branded</span><span>🚐 <strong>Free Pickup</strong></span></div><img src="/images/499031832_24357754093827647_8285045186686109093_n.webp" alt="HVAC van wrap installation by Chicago Fleet Wraps — Precision Today heating and cooling" style="width:100%;border-radius:8px;margin:0 0 24px" loading="lazy"><h2>Why HVAC Companies Need Van Wraps</h2><p class="body-text">HVAC service vans are uniquely positioned for maximum advertising impact. Unlike delivery vehicles that stop briefly, HVAC vans park in residential driveways for 2–8 hours during installations and service calls. Every neighbor walking their dog, every parent on the school run, every mail carrier sees your brand — and remembers it when their furnace breaks down in January or their AC fails in July.</p><p class="body-text">Chicago's extreme seasons drive year-round HVAC demand. A professionally wrapped van generates 30,000–70,000 daily impressions at just $0.04 CPM — compared to $3.50+ CPM for Google Ads and $8–$25 per lead on Angi or HomeAdvisor. One wrapped van pays for itself with a single job referral.</p><h2>HVAC Van Types We Wrap</h2><ul class="services"><li><em>Ford Transit</em> — Full-size and Transit Connect. Most popular HVAC service van in Chicago.</li><li><em>Ram ProMaster</em> — 1500, 2500, 3500 cargo and cutaway models.</li><li><em>Chevy Express</em> — 2500 and 3500 cargo vans for service techs.</li><li><em>Mercedes Sprinter</em> — Standard and high-roof. Ideal for HVAC companies with large equipment.</li><li><strong>Nissan NV200 / NV2500</strong> — Compact and full-size for residential service calls.</li><li><em>Ford E-Series</em> — E-250 and E-350 classic cargo vans.</li></ul><img src="/images/sbc_hvac_van.webp" alt="SBC HVAC van wrap — heating and cooling vehicle graphics Chicago" style="width:100%;border-radius:8px;margin:0 0 24px" loading="lazy"><h2>HVAC Van Wrap Pricing</h2><ul class="services"><li><strong>Full Cargo Van Wrap</strong> — $2,800–$4,500 depending on van size and design complexity.</li><li><strong>Sprinter Van Full Wrap</strong> — $3,500–$5,200 for standard and high-roof models.</li><li><strong>Partial Van Wrap</strong> — $1,500–$2,800 covering 40–60% of the vehicle.</li><li><strong>Van Lettering & Graphics</strong> — $800–$1,500 for logo, phone, and basic info.</li><li><strong>Fleet Discounts</strong> — 5% off 3–4 vans, 10% off 5–9 vans, 15% off 10+ vans.</li></ul><p class="body-text">All HVAC van wraps are <strong>100% tax deductible</strong> under IRS Section 179 as a business advertising expense.</p>
